history.text: Hi
Let's chat!
Hi!
Have you seen the movie Wolf of Wall Street directed by Martin Scorsese?
No, I haven't watch that movie.
Have you?
It's worth a watch. It's a black comedy starring Leonardo DiCaprio and Jonah Hill about a stockbroker's firm engaged in rampant corruption and fraud on Wall Street
Sound's interesting. What is the rating of this movie in Rotten Tomatoes?
I have, I'd recommend it. Rotten tomatoes only gave it 78%, but it's still a passing score.
Yeah, its not a bad rating at all. What year does this movie released?
It was released in 2013. I common criticism is that it glorifies the behavior in the film, but if that's the type of thing you could find comedy in, you would enjoy it.
Sounds great! Aside from Leonardo DiCaprio. Who are the other casts of this movie?
You have Margot Robbie who looked stunning in the move. You also have a Matthew McConaughey, Rob Riener, Kyle Chandler and Jon Favreau. Solid cast
Yeah, solid casts indeed. What is your favorite part of this movie?
It takes place in 1987 and is based the memoir of Jordan Belfort, so the story is loosely true. I enjoyed watching how quickly everything changed once they made a small fortune.
Do you think it is based in real life event?
Some of it is. Especially the beginning where Jordan Belfast starts a small boiler room broker firm in Long Island specializing in penny stocks, that eventually makes a small fortune.

Do you think DiCaprio did a great job in acting his role as Jordan Belfort
?
DiCaprio definitely had the face and character for the type of Wall Street stockbroker who ends up getting in some trouble with the law. He was good
Sounds good. What is the genre of this movie?
It's technically a black comedy. There's definitely some drama and thrill, in it as well as their is an FBI investigation and money laundering schemes
Oh, I love comedy movies. Maybe I will like this one. Tell me about the ending of this movie.
Well DiCaprio's character ends making a move that couldn't be ignored by the FBI and hides money in his in-laws oversees account. Can you guess where it ends up going?
Maybe he got jailed.
Am I correct?
Sort of! His in-laws turn him on when they get caught on something unrelated. Then DiCaprio actually becomes an informant and agrees to gather evidence on his colleagues.
Who is the director of this movie?
Martin Scorsese.
Actually Leo did up jail because he told his colleagues he was an informant
So you were reight
right*
What is the business of Jordan Belfort in this movie?
He is founder of a brokerage firm that operates basic pump and dump scams
Great!
